    Privacy Policy for ${Indian facts} on the Google Assistant

The content for ${Indian facts} has been developed by ${Aryan singh}. However, ${Indian facts} runs on systems provided by Google, and ${Aryan singh} does not have full access to the app. In particular, ${Aryan singh} has no ability to access the messages you send to ${Indian facts} or the responses that it sends back to you.

${Aryan singh} may receive from Google non-personally identifying information about the use of ${Indian facts}. For instance, ${Aryan singh} can access usage information regarding how many users are using the app, which geographical regions they are located in, and basic data including users’ language, device type, and length and frequency of use. None of the information ${Aryan singh} receives from Google identifies you, nor does it reveal to ${Aryan singh} what information you sent to the app or what specific responses the app sent to you.

When you use ${Indian facts}, you are also using the Google Assistant, and the Google Privacy Policy describes how Google collects and uses data about your use of the app. You may wish to consult Google’s documentation regarding what information is shared with your Google Assistant and how to delete your Google Assistant activity.

${Aryan singh} may, in the future, modify ${Indian facts} to run on infrastructure which ${Aryan singh} has full access to, which would allow ${Aryan singh} access to additional information about your interaction with the app. Should that occur, ${Aryan singh} will comply with its obligations under applicable privacy law, including updating this Privacy Policy as required.


